The article reports on several nominations that have been sent to the Senate. Marvin L. Adams from Texas has been nominated to be the Deputy Administrator for Defense Programs at the National Nuclear Security Administration, replacing Charles P. Verdon. Michael Cottman Morgan from Wisconsin has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of Commerce, replacing Neil Jacobs. Laura Gore Ross from New York has been nominated for reappointment as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Corey Wiggins from Mississippi has been nominated to be the Federal Cochairperson of the Delta Regional Authority, replacing Christopher Caldwell.